        id: 'cursor-adv-4', slug: 'background-agents', moduleSlug: 'advanced', toolSlug: 'cursor',
        title: 'Background Agents & Parallel Workflows', description: 'Run multiple AI agents in parallel and manage long-running tasks.',
        order: 4, xpReward: 75, estimatedMinutes: 16,
        content: [
          { type: 'markdown', content: '# Background Agents & Parallel Workflows\n\nCursor supports running multiple AI agents simultaneously, each working on different parts of your project. This enables parallel development workflows that dramatically increase throughput.\n\n## Running Parallel Agents\n\nOpen multiple Composer panels (Cmd/Ctrl+I) and give each one a different task:\n\n- **Agent 1**: "Refactor the auth module to use OAuth 2.0"\n- **Agent 2**: "Fix the failing integration tests in tests/api/"\n- **Agent 3**: "Add loading states to all data-fetching components"\n\nEach agent works independently, and you can switch between them to review progress.\n\n## Background Agent Workflows\n\nBackground agents continue working while you code in other files. This is ideal for:\n\n- **Long-running refactors**: kick off a large refactoring task and continue your own work\n- **Test generation**: have an agent write tests while you implement features\n- **Documentation**: run a docs agent in the background while you code\n- **Bug investigation**: let an agent trace through code while you work on other bugs' },
          { type: 'markdown', content: '## Managing Multiple Agents\n\n- **Review diffs carefully**: each agent makes changes independently, so review for conflicts\n- **Use git branches**: work in separate branches when agents modify the same codebase\n- **Check for conflicts**: if two agents modify the same file, resolve conflicts before applying both\n\n## Composer Model Selection\n\nCursor\'s Composer model is optimized for fast iteration:\n\n- Generations feel near-instant, so you don\'t hesitate to rerun plans or experiments\n- Choose between OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, and Cursor\'s own models\n- Use faster models for simple tasks, more capable models for complex ones\n\n## Advanced: Visual Editor Integration\n\nThe Visual Editor lets you interact with a rendered web app directly:\n\n- **Point and prompt**: click on a UI element and describe changes\n- **Drag and drop**: move elements within the rendered preview\n- **Visual sliders**: adjust properties like spacing, colors, and sizes visually\n\nCombine the Visual Editor with Agent Mode for rapid UI iteration.' },
          { type: 'callout', variant: 'warning', content: 'When running multiple agents on the same project, be careful about file conflicts. Review all changes before accepting, and use git to manage concurrent modifications.' },
        ],
