        id: 'cursor-adv-10', slug: 'keyboard-shortcuts-productivity', moduleSlug: 'advanced', toolSlug: 'cursor',
        title: 'Keyboard Shortcuts & Productivity', description: 'Master power-user shortcuts and workflows for maximum speed in Cursor.',
        order: 10, xpReward: 85, estimatedMinutes: 18,
        content: [
          { type: 'markdown', content: '# Keyboard Shortcuts & Productivity\n\nCursor inherits all VS Code shortcuts and adds AI-specific ones. Mastering these shortcuts eliminates the friction between thinking and executing, making AI interactions feel instant.\n\n## Essential AI Shortcuts\n\n| Shortcut (Mac) | Shortcut (Windows/Linux) | Action |\n|----------------|--------------------------|--------|\n| `Cmd+L` | `Ctrl+L` | Open AI Chat panel |\n| `Cmd+I` | `Ctrl+I` | Open Composer |\n| `Cmd+K` | `Ctrl+K` | Inline Edit (edit code in place) |\n| `Cmd+Shift+L` | `Ctrl+Shift+L` | Add selection to chat context |\n| `Cmd+Shift+K` | `Ctrl+Shift+K` | Generate inline with instructions |\n| `Tab` | `Tab` | Accept AI suggestion |\n| `Esc` | `Esc` | Dismiss AI suggestion |\n| `Cmd+Shift+I` | `Ctrl+Shift+I` | Toggle Composer panel |\n| `Cmd+.` | `Ctrl+.` | Quick fix with AI |\n| `Cmd+Enter` | `Ctrl+Enter` | Send message in Chat/Composer |\n\n## The Inline Edit Workflow (Cmd+K)\n\nInline Edit is the fastest way to make targeted changes:\n\n1. **Select code** you want to change\n2. Press **Cmd+K** — a prompt bar appears above the selection\n3. Type a short instruction: "add error handling", "make async", "extract to function"\n4. Press **Enter** — the code is replaced in place\n5. Press **Cmd+Shift+Enter** to accept, or **Esc** to reject\n\nThis is faster than Chat for single-location edits because you never leave your code.' },
          { type: 'code', language: 'typescript', code: '// Before: Select this function and press Cmd+K\n// Instruction: "add input validation and error handling"\nfunction divide(a: number, b: number): number {\n  return a / b;\n}\n\n// After: Cursor replaces it inline\nfunction divide(a: number, b: number): number {\n  if (typeof a !== \'number\' || typeof b !== \'number\') {\n    throw new TypeError(\'Both arguments must be numbers\');\n  }\n  if (b === 0) {\n    throw new RangeError(\'Cannot divide by zero\');\n  }\n  return a / b;\n}', filename: 'inline-edit-example.ts' },
          { type: 'markdown', content: '## Speed Workflows\n\n### 1. The Select-Ask-Apply Loop\n\nThe fastest debugging workflow:\n1. **Select** the buggy code\n2. **Cmd+L** to open chat with selection as context\n3. Ask "What\'s wrong with this code?"\n4. Click **Apply** on the fix\n\nTime: ~10 seconds for simple bugs.\n\n### 2. The Terminal Fix Flow\n\n1. Run a command that errors in the integrated terminal\n2. Cursor shows a **"Fix with AI"** button next to the error\n3. Click it — Cursor opens Composer with the error context\n4. Accept the fix\n\n### 3. The Multi-Cursor AI Edit\n\n1. Use **Cmd+D** to select multiple occurrences of a pattern\n2. Press **Cmd+K** for an inline edit\n3. Type: "rename to newName" or "add type annotation"\n4. All occurrences are updated simultaneously\n\n### 4. Chat History Navigation\n\n- **Cmd+Up/Down** in chat: cycle through your previous prompts\n- Reuse and refine prompts without retyping\n- Build a personal library of effective prompts over time\n\n## Custom Keybindings\n\nCustomize Cursor\'s AI keybindings in Settings > Keyboard Shortcuts. Commonly customized:\n\n| Default | Common Rebind | Reason |\n|---------|---------------|--------|\n| `Cmd+K` | `Cmd+Shift+E` | Avoid conflict with VS Code\'s Cmd+K combos |\n| `Cmd+L` | `Cmd+J` | Easier one-hand reach |\n| `Cmd+I` | `Cmd+Shift+Space` | Distinct from other shortcuts |' },
          { type: 'callout', variant: 'tip', content: 'Practice the Cmd+K inline edit workflow until it\'s muscle memory. Most developers underuse it because they default to Chat. For single-location edits, inline edit is 3-5x faster than opening a chat conversation.' },
        ],
